he first single from their album ''[[Still Feels Good]]''.  The song became their eighth number-one hit on the Hot Country Songs Chart the week of September 16, 2007. The song was co-written by [[Kenny Chesney]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cmt.com/artists/news/1563929/20070702/rascal_flatts.jhtml |title=Rascal Flatts' New Single Co-Written by Kenny Chesney |accessdate=2008-09-07 |work=cmt.com}}</ref> along with [[Neil Thrasher]] (who also co-wrote Rascal Flatts' 2003 single \"[[I Melt]]\") and [[Wendell Mobley]].\n\n==Charts==\nFor the week of September 22, 2007, the song became the group's third consecutive number one hit.\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (2007)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcountrysongs|1|artist=Rascal Flatts|artistid=395934}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardhot100|19|artist=Rascal Flatts|artistid=395934}}\n|-\n|US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Pop 100]]\n|align=\"center\"|33\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcanadianhot100|49|artist=Rascal Flatts|artistid=395934}}\n|}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2007)\n!scope=\"col\"|Position\n|-\n| US [[Hot Country Songs|Country Songs]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2007/hot-country-songs| title=Best of 2007: Country Songs | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] | date=2007| accessdate=December 13, 2007}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" | 5\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|rascal-flatts|take-me-there}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Rascal Flatts singles}}\n\n[[Category:2007 singles]]\n[[Category:2007 songs]]\n[[Category:Rascal Flatts songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot Country Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Neil Thrasher]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Shaun Silva]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Kenny Chesney]]\n[[Category:Songs written by